Probabilistic Methods, Theory.

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the use of wavelets in nonparametric regression and local spectral density estimation, which involve probabilistic methods.

Theory: The paper reviews the basics of the discrete wavelet transform and describes the construction of an inverse of the stationary wavelet transform, which are theoretical concepts. The paper also discusses the potential use of the stationary wavelet transform as an exploratory statistical method.
